1. A WALNUT looks just like a little brain. Even the wrinkles or folds on the nut are similar to those of the neo-cortex. Walnuts help in the development of over three dozen neuron-transmitters within the brain enhancing the signaling and encouraging new messaging link between the brain cells.

2. ONIONS look like the body cells. Research shows that onions clear waste materials from all of the body cells. They even produce tears which wash the epithelial layers of the eyes.

3. GINGER looks like the stomach and it also aids in digestion. Indians and Chinese have been using it for over 5000 years to calm an upset stomach  cure nausea and motion sickness. It also slows down the growth rate of bowel tumors.

4. A sliced CARROT looks like the human eye. According to experts  eating carrots greatly enhances blood flow to the eyes. Carrots get their orange colour from a plant chemical called beta-carotene  which reduces the risk of developing cataracts.

5. GRAPES resemble the alveoli of the lungs. The lungs are made of branches of ever-smaller airways that finish up with tiny branches of tissue called alveoli. These structures allow oxygen to pass from the lungs to the blood stream. A diet high in fresh grapes has shown to reduce the risk of lung cancer and emphysema.

7. KIDNEY BEANS actually heal and help maintain kidney function and are shaped exactly like human kidneys (hence  their name). Kidney beans provide a variety of minerals and vitamins  which is why they are generally beneficial for your health.

8. MUSHROOMS when sliced in half resembles the shape of the human ear. Mushrooms improve hearing ability  since they contain Vitamin D  which is also healthy for bones.

9. AVOCADOS are good for health and functioning of the womb and cervix in females and look just like these organs.

main_text: Grapes!Our second year of these beautiful black grapes fruiting.I was super nervous about pruning it because I had zero experience with growing grapes (and plenty of eating them which I hoped and intended to do much more of!). However after reading loads of articles and watching plenty of videos of pruning and growing grapes I got the confidence to try.It turns out that grapes are pretty easy to prune and very feisty in regrowing and adding heaps of foliage (leaves and branches) so it’s been much easier and less stressful than I expected. Training them onto our trellis and completing a winter pruning and several(!) summer prunings (yup they grow that enthusiastically!) has been really fun and now they’re fruiting really nicely!#threetreespermaculture #grapes #permaculture #nepalpermaculture #regenerativeagriculture #organic #permacultura #farmstay #wwoof #nepalfarmstay
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "threetreespermaculture"  "comment_text": "Grapes!

Our second year of these beautiful black grapes fruiting.

I was super nervous about pruning it because I had zero experience with growing grapes (and plenty of eating them which I hoped and intended to do much more of!). However  after reading loads of articles and watching plenty of videos of pruning and growing grapes I got the confidence to try.

It turns out that grapes are pretty easy to prune and very feisty in regrowing and adding heaps of foliage (leaves and branches) so it’s been much easier and less stressful than I expected. Training them onto our trellis and completing a winter pruning and several(!) summer prunings (yup  they grow that enthusiastically!) has been really fun and now they’re fruiting really nicely!

#threetreespermaculture #grapes #permaculture #nepalpermaculture #regenerativeagriculture #organic #permacultura #farmstay #wwoof #nepalfarmstay"}}

main_text: ぶどうの花が咲いている姿はチリチリと燃えているように見えます。燃えているように開花している間に手入れをしてあげないと「花ぶるい」といって結実しません。まさに導火線に火が着き、手入れが遅ければ燃え尽きて真っ白な灰になってしまう感覚です。ちなみに花ぶるいを起こし軸だけになってしまった花穂はマッチ棒と比喩されることもあります。開花し、これから忙しくなる状況を「畑が点火した」忙しさピークの状況を「畑が燃えている」手入れが間に合わない状況を「畑が炎上した」もう畑がどうしようもない状況を自分の状態と合わせて「燃え尽きた」これを我が家では隠語として使っていきます。#ぶどうのガーデン #ぶどう #ぶどう農家 #農業  #新規就農 #移住 #山梨 #farm #agriculture #fruit #grapes
comment:
{"1": {"comment_id": "budounogarden"  "comment_text": "ぶどうの花が咲いている姿はチリチリと燃えているように見えます。
燃えているように開花している間に手入れをしてあげないと「花ぶるい」といって結実しません。
まさに導火線に火が着き、手入れが遅ければ燃え尽きて真っ白な灰になってしまう感覚です。
ちなみに花ぶるいを起こし軸だけになってしまった花穂はマッチ棒と比喩されることもあります。

開花し、これから忙しくなる状況を「畑が点火した」
忙しさピークの状況を「畑が燃えている」
手入れが間に合わない状況を「畑が炎上した」
もう畑がどうしようもない状況を自分の状態と合わせて「燃え尽きた」
これを我が家では隠語として使っていきます。

#ぶどうのガーデン #ぶどう #ぶどう農家 #農業  #新規就農 #移住 #山梨 #farm #agriculture #fruit #grapes"}}
